Teams of rescue workers firefighters and ambulances meanwhile scrambled to the wooded crash site as authorities evacuated a nearby monastery threatened by a brush fire started by the crash
European Union EU Transport Commissioner Jacques Barrot also expressed his condolences to victims of the crash
The cause for the crash is yet to be known
Cyprus radio and television stations cancelled their daily programs to relay uninterrupted coverage on the crash as people telephoned to seek news or speculate over what might have caused the crash
